name: ndarray
description: An array object represents a multidimensional, homogeneous array of fixed-size items.

name: ndarray.T
description: The transposed array.

name: ndarray.all
description: Returns True if all elements evaluate to True.

name: ndarray.any
description: Returns True if any of the elements of a evaluate to True.

name: ndarray.argmax
description: Return indices of the maximum values along the given axis.

name: ndarray.argmin
description: Return indices of the minimum values along the given axis of a.

name: ndarray.argpartition
description: Returns the indices that would partition this array.

name: ndarray.argsort
description: Returns the indices that would sort this array.

name: ndarray.astype
description: Copy of the array, cast to a specified type.

name: ndarray.base
description: Base object if memory is from some other object.

name: ndarray.byteswap
description: Swap the bytes of the array elements

name: ndarray.choose
description: Use an index array to construct a new array from a set of choices.

name: ndarray.clip
description: Return an array whose values are limited to [min, max].

name: ndarray.compress
description: Return selected slices of this array along given axis.

name: ndarray.conj
description: Complex-conjugate all elements.

name: ndarray.copy
description: Return a copy of the array.

name: ndarray.ctypes
description: An object to simplify the interaction of the array with the ctypes module.

name: ndarray.ctypes
description: An object to simplify the interaction of the array with the ctypes module.

name: ndarray.cumprod
description: Return the cumulative product of the elements along the given axis.

name: ndarray.cumsum
description: Return the cumulative sum of the elements along the given axis.

name: ndarray.data
description: Python buffer object pointing to the start of the array’s data.

name: ndarray.diagonal
description: Return specified diagonals.

name: ndarray.dtype
description: Data-type of the array’s elements.

name: ndarray.dump
description: Dump a pickle of the array to the specified file.

name: ndarray.dumps
description: Returns the pickle of the array as a string.

name: ndarray.fill
description: Fill the array with a scalar value.

name: ndarray.flags
description: Information about the memory layout of the array.

name: ndarray.flat
description: A 1-D iterator over the array.

name: ndarray.flatten
description: Return a copy of the array collapsed into one dimension.

name: ndarray.getfield
description: Returns a field of the given array as a certain type.

name: ndarray.imag
description: The imaginary part of the array.

name: ndarray.item
description: Copy an element of an array to a standard Python scalar and return it.

name: ndarray.itemset
description: Insert scalar into an array (scalar is cast to array’s dtype, if possible)

name: ndarray.itemsize
description: Length of one array element in bytes.

name: ndarray.max
description: Return the maximum along a given axis.

name: ndarray.mean
description: Returns the average of the array elements along given axis.

name: ndarray.min
description: Return the minimum along a given axis.

name: ndarray.nbytes
description: Total bytes consumed by the elements of the array.

name: ndarray.ndim
description: Number of array dimensions.

name: ndarray.nonzero
description: Return the indices of the elements that are non-zero.

name: ndarray.partition
description: Rearranges the elements in the array in such a way that the value of the element in kth position is in the position it would be in a sorted array.

name: ndarray.prod
description: Return the product of the array elements over the given axis

name: ndarray.ptp
description: Peak to peak (maximum - minimum) value along a given axis.

name: ndarray.put
description: Set a.flat[n] = values[n] for all n in indices.

name: ndarray.ravel
description: Return a flattened array.

name: ndarray.real
description: The real part of the array.

name: ndarray.repeat
description: Repeat elements of an array.

name: ndarray.reshape
description: Returns an array containing the same data with a new shape.

name: ndarray.resize
description: Change shape and size of array in-place.

name: ndarray.round
description: Return a with each element rounded to the given number of decimals.

name: ndarray.searchsorted
description: Find indices where elements of v should be inserted in a to maintain order.

name: ndarray.setflags
description: Set array flags WRITEABLE, ALIGNED, (WRITEBACKIFCOPY and UPDATEIFCOPY), respectively.

name: ndarray.shape
description: Tuple of array dimensions.

name: ndarray.size
description: Number of elements in the array.

name: ndarray.sort
description: Sort an array in-place.

name: ndarray.squeeze
description: Remove single-dimensional entries from the shape of a.

name: ndarray.std
description: Returns the standard deviation of the array elements along given axis.

name: ndarray.strides
description: Tuple of bytes to step in each dimension when traversing an array.

name: ndarray.sum
description: Return the sum of the array elements over the given axis.

name: ndarray.swapaxes
description: Return a view of the array with axis1 and axis2 interchanged.

name: ndarray.take
description: Return an array formed from the elements of a at the given indices.

name: ndarray.tobytes
description: Construct Python bytes containing the raw data bytes in the array.

name: ndarray.tofile
description: Write array to a file as text or binary (default).

name: ndarray.tolist
description: Return the array as an a.ndim-levels deep nested list of Python scalars.

name: ndarray.tostring
description: Construct Python bytes containing the raw data bytes in the array.

name: ndarray.trace
description: Return the sum along diagonals of the array.

name: ndarray.transpose
description: Returns a view of the array with axes transposed.

name: ndarray.var
description: Returns the variance of the array elements, along given axis.

name: ndarray.view
description: New view of array with the same data.
